## Expected Actor Resolution Functions  
  
Based on your authentication flow, each resolver would extract identity from different sources:  
  
**resolveSlackActor()**: Verifies Slack signature and extracts user from webhook payload  
```typescript  
async function resolveSlackActor(req) {  
  // Verify x-slack-signature matches payload  
  const payload = JSON.parse(req.body);  
  return {  
    id: payload.user.id,  
    source: "slack",  
    ip: req.headers["x-forwarded-for"]  
  };  
}  
```  
  
**resolveJWTActor()**: Decodes JWT token to get authenticated user  
```typescript  
async function resolveJWTActor(req) {  
  const token = req.headers.authorization.replace("Bearer ", "");  
  const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET);  
  return {  
    id: decoded.userId,  
    source: "web_dashboard",  
    ip: req.headers["x-forwarded-for"]  
  };  
}  
```  
  
**resolveCLIActor()**: Validates CLI token against stored credentials  
```typescript  
async function resolveCLIActor(req) {  
  const token = req.body.cli_token;  
  // Validate token against database  
  return {  
    id: "founder_cli",  
    source: "cli",  
    ip: req.headers["x-forwarded-for"]  
  };  
}  
```  
  
